        "id": 1002790
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-01T10:52:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Suggestion: currentUtilization-\u003eupdate() is called every poll cycle (default 1 second), but TTIMEOUT_LONG in the spec is also 1 second. If the long-running event doesn\u0027t come back before the next poll, registerResponseHandler will return EEXIST and the response is lost.\n\nConsider giving long-running commands a separate, longer polling interval instead of sharing the same cycle as regular sensors, or skipping update() if a previous request is still pending.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 266,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 266,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "1f3be904946f4614fa7e2633bf7b7c8db09fb138",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
